{# ── DISCLOSURE BANNER · ABOVE THE FOLD (Sheet-7 honest-triage). Canonical .disclosure class
     reused. The inBrief above already states the NOT-Intuit boundary directly under the dark
     hero; this banner makes it unmissable a SECOND time and renders the explicit intent-split
     (file/books = us · account/billing/software = Intuit) as a checks-list with the Intuit
     support link. Sheet-7 mandates the disclosure + intent redirect above the fold. ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="qb-support-independent-disclosure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="disclosure disclosure--warn">
      <svg class="disclosure__icon" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#A4660A" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 11v5M12 7.5v.3" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      <div class="disclosure__body"><strong>TechBrot is an independent accounting firm of Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors. We are not Intuit. For account, billing, or subscription issues, contact Intuit directly <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">&rarr;</a></strong> Reaching this firm does not reach Intuit. &ldquo;Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor&rdquo; is a certification this firm holds from Intuit; it does not mean affiliation, endorsement, or sponsorship. This team cannot access your Intuit account, change your subscription, reset your login, or patch the QuickBooks software. What this team does is the accounting work inside your own company file. This page is informational; it is not Intuit support.</div>
    </div>
    <ul class="checks-list" id="qb-support-independent-split">
      <li><strong>Independent help for your own file (this firm):</strong> books that won&rsquo;t reconcile, months behind, a setup done wrong, migration damage, payroll errors inside the file, reports that don&rsquo;t match reality &mdash; the accounting inside your QuickBooks. Fixed fee, named ProAdvisor.</li>
      <li><strong>Intuit, for the account and the software:</strong> Intuit login, password, or two-factor; subscription, renewal, refund, or billing disputes; QuickBooks software bugs, outages, or Intuit-side error codes. <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Go to Intuit support <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a> &mdash; this firm has no access to your Intuit account.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT IT IS · TL;DR prose. ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="qb-support-independent-tldr">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What independent QuickBooks help actually is.</h2>
    </header>
    <p class="prose" id="qb-support-independent-tldr-body">{{ tldr | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-independent-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Independent QuickBooks help, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="qb-support-independent-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT WE FIX THAT INTUIT WON'T/CAN'T · grid-3 buyer-cards. The accounting INSIDE your own
     file — not the software, not the account. Each card routes to a built spoke where one exists. ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-independent-fixes">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Inside your own file</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What we fix that Intuit&rsquo;s support won&rsquo;t &mdash; or can&rsquo;t.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Intuit supports the product and your account. None of that touches the accounting <em>inside</em> your file &mdash; the numbers, the history, the structure. That is exactly where these problems live, and it is what an independent ProAdvisor firm is for.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for f in fixes %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ f.eyebrow | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{% if f.href %}<a href="{{ f.href }}">{{ f.title | safe }}</a>{% else %}{{ f.title | safe }}{% endif %}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ f.body | safe }}</p>
        {%- if f.href %}<a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ f.href }}">{{ f.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>{%- endif %}
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── HOW THE ENGAGEMENT WORKS · process-diagram (three phases). ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-independent-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Free review, written scope, a named ProAdvisor.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">No mystery, no open-ended hourly meter. The path from &ldquo;something&rsquo;s wrong in my file&rdquo; to a fixed-fee fix is the same every time.</p>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for p in process %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ p.when | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ p.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FIXED-FEE FRAMING · canonical pricing only (no hourly, no invented figures). checks-list. ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-independent-pricing">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Fixed fee, scoped in writing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What it costs.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every engagement is a fixed fee agreed in writing before any work starts &mdash; no hourly surprises. The free file review is what sets the number; the ranges below are the typical bands the scope lands in.</p>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list" id="qb-support-independent-pricing-list">
      {%- for tier in pricing %}
      <li><strong>{{ tier.name | safe }} &mdash; {{ tier.range | safe }}.</strong> {{ tier.body | safe }}</li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="prose"><small>Ranges are typical, not quotes. Your written fixed-fee scope follows the free file review. Fees cover the accounting work inside your own QuickBooks file; they do not include Intuit subscription or product costs, which you pay Intuit directly.</small></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CALL BREAKOUT · bofu handoff component (the paid independent lane). ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-independent-breakout">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="call-breakout">
      <div>
        <p class="call-breakout__title">Ready for independent QuickBooks help?</p>
        <p class="call-breakout__sub">A Certified ProAdvisor (independent firm) reviews your own QuickBooks file free, then scopes the fix in writing within 3 business days &mdash; fixed-fee, never hourly. For Intuit account or billing issues, contact Intuit directly.</p>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review">Get the free file review</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · contract Q/A as faq__list; visible list = FAQPage schema (same array). First Q =
     official-support question (Sheet-7). (H2) ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-independent-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Before you reach out.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="qb-support-independent-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="qb-support-independent-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level (founder-name-zero). David survives only as reviewedBy @id in schema. ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-independent-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Independent-firm standards.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <svg class="byline-block__mark" viewBox="0 0 64 64" role="img" aria-label="TechBrot"><rect width="64" height="64" rx="14" fill="#1A1915"></rect><g transform="translate(12.16 12.16) scale(0.62)" fill="#F5F3EC"><path d="M8 10 H38 V54 H26 V22 H8 Z"></path><rect x="42" y="10" width="14" height="12"></rect></g></svg>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>{{ reviewProse | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-18</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-18</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-18 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED · where else to go (grid-2 buyer-cards). The flagship contact-support page ships
     the same proof; the file-review / cleanup / error-codes spokes are built. ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-independent-related">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where else to go.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading"><a href="{{ r.href }}"{% if r.rel %} rel="{{ r.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ r.title | safe }}</a></h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ r.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ r.href }}"{% if r.rel %} rel="{{ r.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ r.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
